  "status": "Final",
  "summary": "[ERC-8001](./eip-8001.md) defines a minimal, single-chain primitive for **multi-party agent coordination**. An initiator posts an intent and each participant provides a verifiable acceptance attestation. Once the required set of acceptances is present and fresh, the intent is executable. The standard specifies typed data, lifecycle, mandatory events, and verification rules compatible with [EIP-712], [ERC-1271], [EIP-2098], and [EIP-5267]. [ERC-8001](./eip-8001.md) omits privacy, reputation, threshold policies, bonding, and cross-chain semantics. Those are expected as optional modules that reference this specification.",
  "title": "Agent Coordination Framework"
}